) was used to calculate Neighbor-Joining NJ trees based on the Kimura 2-parameter (K2P; 
Kimura 1980
) distances (standard for barcoding studies) and pair wise deletion of missing data. The support for tree branches was calculated by the nonparametric bootstrap method (
Felsenstein 1985
) with 1000 replicates and shown next to the branches. Codon positions included were 1st+2nd+3rd+Noncoding. All ambiguous positions were removed for each sequence pair.
